üé® 2. Design & Layout Planning
 Decide the purpose of your site (portfolio, resume, blog, product page, etc.)

 Sketch a layout (paper, Figma, or whiteboard)

 Choose a color palette (use coolors.co or Adobe Color)

 Pick a clean Google Font (e.g., Inter, Roboto, Poppins)

üìÑ 3. HTML Content Structure
 Add basic boilerplate HTML:

html
Copy
Edit
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Your Website Name</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- content here -->
  <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
 Add the following sections to <body> (adjust as needed):

 <header> with a logo & navigation

 <section> for intro/about

 <section> for main content (projects, articles, products, etc.)

 <section> for contact info or form

 <footer> with copyright/social links

üíÖ 4. Styling with CSS
 Set a global style:

css
Copy
Edit
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
body {
  font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
  background-color: #f4f4f4;
  color: #333;
  line-height: 1.6;
}
 Style the layout with flexbox or grid

 Add spacing, hover effects, and responsive typography

 Create mobile-friendly media queries

 Add visual elements: icons (e.g., FontAwesome), borders, shadows, buttons, etc.

üñºÔ∏è 5. Images & Media
 Add a favicon (favicon.ico)

 Use .webp or compressed .jpg/.png for performance

 Place images in /assets/images and reference them in HTML/CSS

 Include alt text for accessibility

üß† 6. Make It Informative
 Write clear headings and summaries

 Use bullet points, lists, or tables to structure information

 Include relevant links (<a href="#">)

 Add charts or infographics if applicable (use Chart.js or embed static ones)

‚öôÔ∏è 7. Interactivity (Optional)
 Use script.js to add:

 Button hover effects

 Scroll animations

 Image sliders, tabs, or collapsible sections

 Consider using a lightweight JS library if needed (e.g., AOS)

üîç 8. Testing & Polish
 Check layout on different screen sizes

 Run through every link and button

 Fix spelling, grammar, or broken visuals

 Validate HTML/CSS at validator.w3.org

